metadata.description:

But wait, there's more to this fantastical journey! Nestled within each digital artwork lies a hidden treasure - an embedded blueprint that holds the secret to crafting a tangible, real-life edition. Picture it: delicate petals brought to life in the physical realm, ready to be gifted or cherished!

metadata.name: Anfractuous #427
metadata.description: The title is quite literally a visual description of the work, as anfractuous means: characterized by windings and turnings; sinuous; circuitous. With this project I aimed to strike a balance between easily recognizable smooth large scale forms and the small fragmented details that populate these forms.

metadata.name: Urban Jungle #87
metadata.description:
A riot of colors and shapes that blend urban art with natural elements. The trees and vibrant hues, seem to burst out of the concrete jungle, challenging the viewer's perception of the boundary between the city and nature. 

Elements are incorporated into the piece, adding to the overall sense of chaos and energy. Despite the seeming discordance, the composition is unified by the use of color and movement. 

"Urban Jungle" captures the raw and untamed spirit of the city, reminding us that even amidst the chaos, there is a kind of beauty to be found.

metadata.name: Syzers #272
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑ On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template.

metadata.name: Harmonious Dissonance #19
metadata.description:
'Harmonious Dissonance' combines vertical lines, dots, and noise to evoke a unique visual experience. The canvas comes alive with a dynamic interplay of elements, creating an atmosphere that balances order and chaos.

Vertical lines stand as pillars of structure within the composition. They impart a sense of stability and direction, drawing the viewer's gaze upward and downward, guiding their exploration of the artwork's intricate details.

Amongst these lines are clusters of dots These dots vary in size and density, adding an element of randomness to the piece. From a distance, they create a harmonious texture, while up close, they reveal a fascinating world of individual nuances.

Flecks and fragments of color and texture emerge from the background. The position of lines are adjusted with noise. This noise disrupts the apparent order of the vertical lines and dots, injecting a hint of controlled chaos. 

'Harmonious Dissonance' melds the precision of vertical lines with the spontaneity of dots and the deliberate disorder of noise. It draws viewers into an ever-evolving dialogue between structure and spontaneity, cohesion and disruption.


Created with p5.js.
This was created as part of the GDAP 2023 Summer Class in Taipei.
